olive oil
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
½ tin chickpeas
1 cucumber
2 radish
½ Onion
½ lemon
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet tahini
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
½ tsp honey
1 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
½ cup water
1 tsp brown sugar
½ bag mint

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Slice mini flour tortillas into strips.
• Place tortilla strips on a lined oven tray (don’t worry if they overlap). Turn with olive oil and season with salt.
• Bake until lightly golden and crispy, 8-10 minutes.

• Drain and rinse chickpeas (see ingredients). Finely chop cucumber, radish and onion (see ingredients). Slice lemon into wedges.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• In a small bowl, combine tahini, Greek-style yoghurt, the honey and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, radish, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste and set aside.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef mince and onion, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 7-8 minutes.
• Add chickpeas, tomato paste and chermoula spice blend and cook, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce pan to medium, add the water and brown sugar and simmer, stirring, until combined, 2-3 minutes. Season to taste.

• Divide tortilla chips between plates and top with Middle Eastern beef and chickpea fatteh.
• Top with cucumber salsa. Tear over mint (see ingredients) and sprinkle with toasted almonds.
• Serve with tahini yoghurt and remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!